        <num>RCW 74.42.250</num>
        <heading>Medication stop ordersâ€”Procedure for persons with developmental disabilities</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_74_42_250__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When the physician's order for medication does not include a specific time limit or a specific number of dosages, the facility shall notify the physician that the medication will be stopped at a date certain unless the medication is ordered continued by the physician. The facility shall so notify the physician every thirty days.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_74_42_250__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A facility for the developmentally disabled shall have an automatic stop order on all drugs, unless such stoppage will place the patient in jeopardy.
[
1979 ex.s. c 211 s 25
.]</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
